    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2003-02-05</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-11-28T17:35:40Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[Small Business Drought Relief Act of 2003 - Amends the Small Business Act to include drought within the definition of "disaster" for purposes of disaster loans provided to small businesses through the Small Business Administration (SBA).<p>Requires the SBA, within 30 days after receiving a State governor's certification that small businesses in that State have suffered economic injury as a result of a disaster, to respond in writing to that governor regarding the extent to which the SBA intends to exercise its authority concerning the provision of disaster loan assistance.]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
